comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-31T19:27:07.242Z",audit-cli-agent,"Phase 1 inspection complete. Reviewed: src/cli/commands/ (all 55+ files), update-many.ts (has rollback/checkpoint/dry-run, uses runUpdate not runClose → cannot trigger close validation), close.ts (supports inline resolution/expected/actual since pr#78), list.ts (has sort/filter/projection/brief/compact modes), context.ts (markdown/toon/json output), stats.ts (totals by_type by_status). Key gaps emerging: (1) close-many does not exist — update-many uses runUpdate which won't trigger close semantics; (2) no pm copy/clone command; (3) no saved/named filter presets; (4) no item tree view (children hierarchy); (5) no watch/subscribe for live updates; (6) history has no per-field diff view. Will run dedup searches before proposing."
  "2026-05-31T19:31:02.232Z",audit-cli-agent,"Phase 2 complete. Dedup searches run for all 8 proposed items + 3 ADRs + 3 stories. No exact duplicates found in closed history. Key confirmed gaps: (1) close-many (no closed item exists; pm-12ib was auto-route for single update->close, unrelated); (2) list --updated-after/--created-after (list.ts only has deadline-before/after); (3) update-many --ids explicit filter (pm-lwps was governance ownership override, different concern); (4) aggregate numeric sum (only count grouping exists); (5) history field-diff view (no item); (6) pm copy/clone (no item); (7) pm list --tree recursive (no item). Exit code ADR is undocumented (constants.ts has EXIT_CODE enum but no Decision item). Ready to write deliverable."
learnings[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-31T19:30:21.811Z",audit-cli-agent,"update-many delegates every mutation to runUpdate (not runClose), so setting --status closed via update-many skips close validation (validate-close), the active-children check, and never populates close_reason properly. A dedicated close-many surface is the clean fix."
  "2026-05-31T19:30:24.290Z",audit-cli-agent,pm list already filters by --parent <id> (line 326 of list.ts) but has no --tree / --recursive flag to render the full subtree as an indented hierarchy. This is a gap for agents navigating epic->feature->task hierarchies.
  "2026-05-31T19:30:29.849Z",audit-cli-agent,"pm list has --deadline-before/--deadline-after filters but no --updated-after / --created-after date filters. Agents doing incremental sync (e.g. 'what changed since my last context pull') must fetch all items and filter client-side, which is expensive on large trackers."
  "2026-05-31T19:30:32.127Z",audit-cli-agent,pm history shows the full event stream for an item but does not compute per-entry field diffs (before/after for each changed field). Agents diagnosing 'what exactly changed in this update' must reconstruct diffs manually from consecutive snapshots.
